===Etymology===
From {{etyl|sa|en}} {{term|sc=Deva|बहुव्रीहि|tr=bahú-vrīhi||much rice|lang=sa}}, itself a bahuvrihi from {{term|sc=Deva|बहु|tr=bahu||much|lang=sa}} and {{term|sc=Deva|व्रीहि|tr=vrīhi||rice|lang=sa}}, referring neither to {{term|much}} nor to {{term|rice}}, but to a person who has much rice, i.e. a rich man, one who has "much rice".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|linguistics|lang=en}} A type of [[nominal]] [[compound]] in which the first part modifies the second and neither part alone retains the intended meaning. Examples include {{term|redcoat}}, {{term|bluestocking}} and {{term|lowlife}}.

